cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the use of Item Response Theory (IRT) in measuring the ability of Machine Learning models, specifically for Recognizing Textual Entailment tasks. This falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP), which is a subfield of Computational Linguistics (CL) and Machine Learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep neural network models (DNNs), which falls under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Computer Vision (CV). Finally, the paper proposes a new training process called fine-tuning, which is a common technique used in Neural Networks (NE). Therefore, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.NE are also likely sub-categories.
